;; README.slat
;; Book of AI Tech Cards — orientation

(readme
  :book "Book of AI Tech Cards"
  :dialect "motoi"
  :one-liner
  "Fourteen cards. Engineering-firm register. Who made what, when, why
   it matters. No ranking. No advice. No product marketing."

  :audience "any — reads at kid level, honest for adults"

  :voice
  "Terse-warm. Motoi's register. Same tone we'd use for DEC, SGI, or
   PARC. Facts first, dates precise, arxiv IDs where they exist.
   Engineering respect in the shape of the prose."

  :companies-in-here
   ((anthropic       "Constitutional AI, MCP, scaling-law work")
    (openai          "GPT lineage, Whisper, CLIP, DALL-E, InstructGPT")
    (google-deepmind "transformer paper, AlphaGo, AlphaFold, Gemini")
    (meta-ai         "PyTorch, Llama open weights")
    (mistral         "efficient LLM research, Mixtral MoE")
    (deepseek        "DeepSeek-V3, reasoning-model research")
    (cohere          "enterprise LLM, RAG-native")
    (xai             "Grok"))

  :technologies-in-here
   ((transformer        "Vaswani et al. 2017, arxiv 1706.03762")
    (mcp                "Model Context Protocol, Anthropic 2024")
    (constitutional-ai  "Anthropic 2022, arxiv 2212.08073")
    (rlhf               "InstructGPT 2022, arxiv 2203.02155")
    (lora               "Microsoft 2021, arxiv 2106.09685")
    (whisper-and-clip   "OpenAI 2022 and 2021"))

  :what-is-NOT-in-here
  "Rankings. Advice. Buyer's guides. `Which model should I use`. Product
   marketing. Predictions about who wins the AI race. Any statement that
   would age within six months.

   Also not in here: firms that have not shipped work that entered the
   engineering stack. This is not a directory of everyone doing AI. It
   is a card set of firms whose work matters to how modern AI got here."

  :provenance
  "Every date, name, and arxiv ID traces to a public source cited in the
   card's :provenance block. Where uncertainty exists, :status
   :needs-alfred-verify. No fabrication. No mythologizing. No hype.")
